      "author": "kehn",
      "published": "2026-07-02T12:02:29Z",
      "bullets": [
        "LLMs exhibit distinct stylistic fingerprints, like overusing specific vocabulary ('delve', 'testament') and predictable narrative structures in synthetic fiction.",
        "Fine-tuning and temperature scaling (e.g., >1.0) help mitigate repetitive structural tropes and predictable token distributions in creative generation tasks.",
        "Detecting machine-generated prose relies on identifying low-entropy transitions and systemic biases in plot pacing inherent to RLHF-aligned models."
      ]
    },
