      "title": "Bad Epoll (CVE-2026-46242)",
      "url": "https://github.com/J-jaeyoung/bad-epoll",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/drf6my",
      "score": 24,
      "comments": 4,
      "author": "dzwdz",
      "published": "2026-07-04T18:40:12Z",
      "bullets": [
        "CVE-2026-46242 exposes a critical vulnerability in the Linux kernel epoll subsystem, risking local privilege escalation or system crashes.",
        "The issue likely involves race conditions or use-after-free flaws during eventpoll file descriptor recycling and concurrent close operations.",
        "Security teams must prioritize Linux kernel updates patching `fs/eventpoll.c` and restrict unprivileged user namespaces to limit exploitation paths."
      ]
    },
